{
  "texts": [
    "To alleviate this problem, a regularization term is used to reduce the weight size of the network or limit the model capacity (Goodfellow et al. 2016).",
    "In GANs, neural networks are used in the generator as well as in the discriminator.",
    "So, when the discriminator produces ambiguous gradients as feedback to the generator continuously, the generator learns to generate similar images again and again to fool the discriminator which leads to the mode collapse problem.",
    "Here, regularization is used as weight normalization.",
    "ing to the normalized weights during the training of GANs (Lee and Seok 2020)."
  ]
}